						<summary>

						<p>On a slab.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">15th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the grant of the village Voṟaūr as <hi rend="italic">yimmaḍi dharma</hi> to Kēśavayya in the presence of the god Aubaḷa of Bāḍa by Mādana yīṁmadi Siga-nāyaka who is described as <hi rend="italic">mahānāyakāchārya.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is in characters of the 15th century A.D.</p>						

